text: Habo Church () is a wooden church building in Habo in Sweden. It was built in 1680, and received its present appearance in 1723. Belonging to Habo Parish of the Church of Sweden, it was depicted at the 2002 Swedish Christmas stamp series "Romantiska kyrkor i juletid" ("Romantic Churches at Christmastime"). == References == ==Other websites== Category:Church of Sweden churches Category:Wooden churches Category:Habo Category:18th-century buildings and structures Category:1680s establishments in Europe
